keyFacts: The document is a comprehensive travel log for Ghislaine Maxwell generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection on September 23, 2019.
It shows Maxwell was an extremely frequent international traveler, with hundreds of recorded flights between 2000 and mid-2019.

Common travel routes included transatlantic flights between the U.S. (especially Boston, New York, Miami) and London, as well as travel to Caribbean destinations and private aviation through Teterboro (TEB).
The last recorded entry is dated June 11, 2019, showing Maxwell using Automated Passport Control at Boston Logan Airport, just months before her arrest in July 2020.
The document includes codes for various ports of entry and inspection types, indicating detailed government tracking of her movements.
